definitions.definition: A local custom or law of a settlement or district.
A rule made by a local authority to regulate its own affairs .

subdefinitions.definition: A numbered provision within such kind of legislation.

definitions.definition: A law or rule governing the internal affairs of an organization (e.g., corporation or business).

main_definition: A local custom or law of a settlement or district.
secondary_definitions: ( often in the plural ) A rule made by a local authority to regulate its own affairs .
A law or rule governing the internal affairs of an organization (e.g., corporation or business).
